This subject focuses on legal remedies for protecting and restoring the rights violated by the public authority and for guaranteeing the reparation of the damage caused. Here the primary legal remedies (such as the action for annulment of an administrative act) as also the claims for the elimination of unlawful consequences and for the compensation for damages are to be mentioned. In addition, the liability of member states under the EC law will be discussed. The course centres upon case studies.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the subject is to give an in-depth knowledge on theoretical foundations, main legal problems and case law of the tort liability of public authorities. This subject also aims to develop students' argumentation skills and to systematically promote the practical competence for solving the cases in this field.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students having participated in this subject: -	Have profound knowledge on the material and procedural conditions of the claims based on the tort liability of public authorities;  -	Are familiar with the conditions of the liability of member states under the EU law and with the relevant case law of the European Court of Justice; -	Are prepared to analyse the main theoretical legal standpoints and case law in this field and are ready to take posititions and make convincing arguments;  -	Recognise the legal problems of the tort liability of public authorities in practice and are skilled to deliver a detailed case study.
